This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to reduce gender bias in abusive language detection models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of pre-trained word embeddings and model architectures, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses bias mitigation methods, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
